<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>90 Day Trial Dismissal — <%- site.businessName %></title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400;500;600&family=Jost:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/service-page.css">
</head>
<body>

  <%- include('../partials/header') %>

  <section class="svc-hero">
    <div class="svc-hero-inner">
      <div class="svc-hero-content">
        <span class="hero-tag">Employment Law</span>
        <h1>90 Day Trial <em>Dismissal</em></h1>
        <p>Being dismissed under a 90 day trial period doesn't always mean your employer acted lawfully. A trial period must meet strict legal requirements to be valid — and many don't.</p>
        <ul class="svc-hero-bullets">
          <li>Trial periods must be correctly set up to be enforceable</li>
          <li>Your employer must still act in good faith</li>
          <li>You may still have options even within a trial period</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-hero-form">
        <p class="form-intro">Find out if your dismissal was lawful</p>
        <%- include("../partials/contact-form.ejs") %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="svc-section svc-define">
    <div class="svc-section-inner">
      <div class="svc-text">
        <span class="section-label">Understanding the issue</span>
        <h2>What is a 90 day trial period?</h2>
        <p>The 90 day trial period provision allows employers to dismiss new employees within the first 90 days of employment without the employee being able to raise a personal grievance for unjustified dismissal. However, this provision comes with strict legal requirements that must be met for the trial period to be valid.</p>
        <p>If your employer has failed to comply with any of these requirements, the trial period may be unenforceable — meaning you could still have the right to raise a personal grievance despite being dismissed within 90 days.</p>
        <p>Even where a valid trial period exists, your employer must still act in good faith and cannot use the trial period as a shield to discriminate against you or dismiss you for unlawful reasons.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-callout">
        <div class="svc-callout-inner">
          <span class="callout-label">Did you know?</span>
          <p>Many 90 day trial dismissals are successfully challenged because the trial period was <strong>not correctly included</strong> in the employment agreement before the employee started work, or the agreement was not signed in time.</p>
          <a href="#contact" class="btn-primary">Get a free assessment</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="svc-section svc-help">
    <div class="svc-section-inner svc-section-inner--centered">
      <div class="svc-section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Our approach</span>
        <h2>How we can help you</h2>
        <p>We scrutinise the validity of your trial period and explore every available avenue to protect your rights.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-help-grid">
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h11"/></svg></div><h3>Trial period review</h3><p>We carefully review your employment agreement and the circumstances of your dismissal to assess whether the trial period was validly established.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg></div><h3>Grievance assessment</h3><p>Even within a trial period, you may have grounds for a grievance on other bases such as discrimination or breach of good faith.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/></svg></div><h3>Negotiation</h3><p>We can negotiate with your former employer on your behalf to reach a resolution, even where formal grievance rights are limited.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg></div><h3>Urgent advice</h3><p>Time limits still apply. We provide urgent advice to ensure you don't miss any deadlines that could affect your options.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="23"/><path d="M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 000 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 010 7H6"/></svg></div><h3>Compensation pursuit</h3><p>Where we identify a valid claim, we pursue the best possible outcome including lost wages and compensation.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-help-card"><div class="svc-help-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 01-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 01-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 013 6.18 2 2 0 015 4h3a2 2 0 012 1.72z"/></svg></div><h3>Ongoing support</h3><p>We keep you informed throughout the process and are available to answer your questions at every stage.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="svc-section svc-process">
    <div class="svc-section-inner svc-section-inner--centered">
      <div class="svc-section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Step by step</span>
        <h2>What the process looks like</h2>
        <p>Here is what happens when you come to us after a 90 day trial dismissal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-steps">
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">01</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Contact us immediately</h3><p>Time limits may still apply. Contact us as soon as possible after your dismissal so we can advise you on your options.</p></div></div>
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">02</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Document review</h3><p>We review your employment agreement, offer letter, and any correspondence to assess the validity of the trial period.</p></div></div>
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">03</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Honest assessment</h3><p>We give you a clear and honest assessment of whether you have viable grounds to challenge the dismissal.</p></div></div>
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">04</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Raise a grievance</h3><p>If grounds exist, we raise a formal personal grievance with your employer on your behalf.</p></div></div>
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">05</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Mediation or negotiation</h3><p>We represent you through mediation or direct negotiation to reach the best possible outcome.</p></div></div>
        <div class="svc-step"><div class="svc-step-num">06</div><div class="svc-step-content"><h3>Resolution</h3><p>We work to secure compensation, a reference, or other remedies appropriate to your circumstances.</p></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="svc-section svc-restrictions">
    <div class="svc-section-inner">
      <div class="svc-text">
        <span class="section-label">Before you proceed</span>
        <h2>Restrictions &amp; disqualifiers</h2>
        <p>The 90 day trial period is a significant limitation on employee rights, but it is not absolute. Understanding the boundaries is key.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="svc-restrict-grid">
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--warn"><h3>Agreement must be signed first</h3><p>The trial period clause must be in your employment agreement and signed before you start work. If you signed after your first day, the clause may be invalid.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--warn"><h3>New employees only</h3><p>Trial periods can only apply to employees who have not previously been employed by that employer. If you've worked for them before, the clause may not apply.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--warn"><h3>No discrimination</h3><p>Even within a valid trial period, your employer cannot dismiss you for discriminatory reasons such as pregnancy, religion, ethnicity, or disability.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--warn"><h3>Notice must be given</h3><p>Your employer must still provide the notice period specified in your agreement when dismissing you under a trial period.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--warn"><h3>90 day time limit still applies</h3><p>If you have grounds to challenge the dismissal, you must still raise a personal grievance within 90 days of the dismissal.</p></div>
        <div class="svc-restrict-card svc-restrict-card--info"><h3>Don't assume you have no options</h3><p>Many trial period dismissals are successfully challenged. Contact us for a free review of your agreement and circumstances before giving up on your claim.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <div class="contact-inner">
      <div class="contact-info">
        <span class="section-label">Get in touch</span>
        <h2>Dismissed under a trial period?</h2>
        <p>Don't assume you have no recourse. Contact us today for a free review of your situation — many trial period dismissals are successfully challenged.</p>
        <div class="contact-detail">
          <div class="contact-item"><div class="contact-item-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 01-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 01-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 013 6.18 2 2 0 015 4h3a2 2 0 012 1.72 12.84 12.84 0 00.7 2.81 2 2 0 01-.45 2.11L9.09 11.91a16 16 0 006 6l1.27-1.27a2 2 0 012.11-.45 12.84 12.84 0 002.81.7A2 2 0 0122 18z"/></svg></div><div class="contact-item-text"><span>Phone</span><a href="tel:<%- site.phoneTel %>"><%- site.phone %></a></div></div>
          <div class="contact-item"><div class="contact-item-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg></div><div class="contact-item-text"><span>Email</span><a href="mailto:<%- site.email %>"><%- site.email %></a></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="contact-form">
        <div id="form-success" class="form-message form-message--success" style="display:none;">Thank you! Your message has been sent. We will be in touch shortly.</div>
        <div id="form-error" class="form-message form-message--error" style="display:none;">Something went wrong. Please try again or call us directly.</div>
        <form id="contact-form" novalidate>
          <input type="hidden" name="service" value="90 Day Trial Dismissal">
          <div class="form-row">
            <div class="form-group"><label for="fname">First name</label><input type="text" id="fname" name="fname" placeholder="Jane" required></div>
            <div class="form-group"><label for="lname">Last name</label><input type="text" id="lname" name="lname" placeholder="Smith" required></div>
          </div>
          <div class="form-group"><label for="email">Email address</label><input type="email" id="email" name="email" placeholder="jane@example.com" required></div>
          <div class="form-group"><label for="phone">Phone number</label><input type="tel" id="phone" name="phone" placeholder="021 000 0000"></div>
          <div class="form-group"><label for="message">Message</label><textarea id="message" name="message" placeholder="Briefly describe your situation..." required></textarea></div>
          <button type="submit" class="form-submit" id="form-btn">Send enquiry</button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
